---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Research" description="Research interests, affiliations, and ongoing projects – Felipe Lamarca">
  <div class="space-y-12">
    <header>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl font-medium text-ink dark:text-ink-dark mb-2">Research</h1>
      <p class="text-ink-secondary dark:text-ink-secondary-dark">Research interests, affiliations, and ongoing projects</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section-title">Affiliations</h2>

      <div class="space-y-10">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-accent dark:border-accent-dark pl-5 space-y-1">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-medium text-ink dark:text-ink-dark flex items-center gap-3 flex-wrap">
            Data Scientist <span class="text-ink-muted dark:text-ink-muted-dark font-normal">@</span>
            <a href="https://atlasintel.org/" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">AtlasIntel</a>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-ink-secondary dark:text-ink-secondary-dark leading-relaxed">
            AtlasIntel provides advanced data products for political intelligence and economic forecasting. My work involves calibrating survey samples, political analysis, public opinion monitoring, and improving internal data pipelines.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-accent dark:border-accent-dark pl-5 space-y-4">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-medium text-ink dark:text-ink-dark">Researcher <span class="text-ink-muted dark:text-ink-muted-dark font-normal">@</span> IESP-UERJ</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-ink dark:text-ink-dark">
                <a href="https://mape.org.br/" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MAPE</a>
                <span class="text-ink-muted dark:text-ink-muted-dark font-normal text-sm ml-1">· coordinated by Fernando Meireles &amp; Bruno Schaefer</span>
              </p>
              <p class="text-ink-secondary dark:text-ink-secondary-dark text-sm mt-1 leading-relaxed">Policy and Election Monitoring and Evaluation Laboratory. Dedicated to studying public policy, elections, and their interconnections using causal inference and machine learning techniques.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-ink dark:text-ink-dark">
                <a href="https://www.lab-doxa.org.br/" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">DOXA</a>
                <span class="text-ink-muted dark:text-ink-muted-dark font-normal text-sm ml-1">· coordinated by Fernando Meireles &amp; Argelina Cheibub Figueiredo</span>
              </p>
              <p class="text-ink-secondary dark:text-ink-secondary-dark text-sm mt-1 leading-relaxed">Laboratory of Electoral Studies, Political Communication and Public Opinion. A leading center for research on electoral processes, political communication, and voting behavior in Brazil.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-ink dark:text-ink-dark">
                <a href="http://necon.iesp.uerj.br" class="link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NECON</a>
                <span class="text-ink-muted dark:text-ink-muted-dark font-normal text-sm ml-1">· coordinated by Fabiano Santos</span>
              </p>
              <p class="text-ink-secondary dark:text-ink-secondary-dark text-sm mt-1 leading-relaxed">Center for Studies on Congress. Focused on academic research on the Brazilian legislature, including databases on nominal votes, party migration, and legislative production.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-ink-secondary dark:text-ink-secondary-dark leading-relaxed mt-8 text-sm">
        Before joining AtlasIntel, MAPE, DOXA, and NECON, I provided data science and research consulting services to both industry (Roberto Marinho Foundation, Artplan, Visagio) and academia (FGV EBAPE, CEBRAP, GENI/UFF). See my <a href="/cv" class="link">CV</a> for a full record of my professional experience.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section-title">Ongoing Projects</h2>
      <div class="divide-y divide-border dark:divide-border-dark">
        <div class="py-4">
          <p class="font-medium text-ink dark:text-ink-dark">A Systematic Review of Text-as-Data Approaches to Parliamentary Behavior</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink-secondary dark:text-ink-secondary-dark mt-1 leading-relaxed">A structured, reproducible review of how computational text methods have been used to study legislative organization. The paper applies text-as-data tools to the review process itself, using abstract embeddings to map the field semantically. To be presented at XIII ALACIP (Buenos Aires, 2026).</p>
          <div class="mt-2 text-sm">
            <a href="/publications" class="link">See in Publications →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="py-4">
          <p class="font-medium text-ink dark:text-ink-dark">Da gaveta ao plenário: os caminhos da aprovação de pautas na Câmara dos Deputados</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink-secondary dark:text-ink-secondary-dark mt-1 leading-relaxed">An analysis of the determinants of agenda approval in the Brazilian Chamber of Deputies, combining quantitative analysis of legislative proposals with party coordination indicators. Joint work with Lucas Calabró Berti (IESP-UERJ). To be presented at ABCP 2026.</p>
          <div class="mt-2 text-sm">
            <a href="/publications" class="link">See in Publications →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="py-4">
          <p class="font-medium text-ink dark:text-ink-dark">Quantos votos meu partido vai fazer? Prevendo o vote share nos municípios brasileiros</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink-secondary dark:text-ink-secondary-dark mt-1 leading-relaxed">A predictive model for party vote share at the municipal level in Brazil, drawing on electoral geography and party organization. Joint work with Tomás Paixão (IESP-UERJ).</p>
          <div class="mt-2 text-sm">
            <a href="/publications" class="link">See in Publications →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
